Title : Kreidler Florett RS
Text : {{Orphan|date=August 2016}}

[[File:Kreidler Florett RS Baujahr 1970.jpeg|thumb|Kreidler Florett RS (1970)]]

'''Kreidler Florett RS''' was a German [[moped]] of ''[[Kreidler|Kreidler's Metall- und Drahtwerke G.m.b.H.]]'' in [[Kornwestheim]] near [[Stuttgart]] (Germany), of which 125,000 pieces have been built between 1967 and 1981.<ref>Frank O. Hrachowy: ''Kreidler.'' Pages 147–150.</ref> The mark ''Florett RS'' was the fastest of Kreidler and in comparison to ''Hercules K 50'' and ''Zündapp KS 50'' an equally good choice.

==Specifications==
Small [[motorcycle]]s with up to 50&nbsp;cm³ capacity were exempt from taxes and licence plates and could be driven with a Class 4 driving licence with a minimum age of 16 years. To stop the competitive spiral, the three leading manufactureres Kreidler, Hercules and Zündapp agreed 1970 to a voluntary limitation of the 50-cm³ class to 6,25&nbsp;[[Pferdestärke#PS|PS]] and a gearbox with a maximum of 5 gears.<ref name="Schw">Waldemar Schwarz: [http://www.motorradonline.de/vergleichstest/auf-achse-hercules-k-50-se-kreidler-florett-rs-leistungsmessung-fahreindruecke/214606?seite=2 ''Leistungswettlauf''] on motorradonline.de of 6. June 2008. Downloaded on 20 April 2014.</ref>

==Bibliography==
* Frank O. Hrachowy: ''Kreidler. Geschichte-Typen-Technik.'' (in German) 1. Auflage. Verlag Johann Kleine Vennekate, Lemgo 2009, {{ISBN|978-3-935517-45-4}}.

